@subsection		fbformat10bitycbcr	10-Bit YCbCr Format

This format, identified by the \c NTV2_FBF_10BIT_YCBCR enumeration constant, has twelve 10-bit unsigned components that are packed into four 32-bit little-endian words.
(Six pixels are represented in each 16 bytes.) This is the format used by Quicktime to store 10-bit YCbCr video and is referred to (in both QuickTime and Windows)
as the 'v210' "FourCC" format.

