@subsection		fbformats8bitdvcpro	8-Bit DVCPro

This format, identified by the \c NTV2_FBF_8BIT_DVCPRO enumeration constant, is a popular lossy 4:1:1 compression scheme.

@subsection		fbformats8bithdv		8-Bit HDV

This format, identified by the \c NTV2_FBF_8BIT_HDV enumeration constant, is a lossy H.262/MPEG-2 (video) and MPEG-1 Layer 2 (audio) compression scheme.

@subsection		fbformats10bitcion	10-Bit Raw YCbCr (CION)

This format, identified by the \c NTV2_FBF_10BIT_RAW_YCBCR enumeration constant, is used for raw RGB Bayer capture from the AJA CION camera.
Bayer pixels are 10-bit resolution stored in big-endian packed format, as required by the 'DNG' (TIFF) file specification.
The packing cadence is 16 Bayer pixels in 20 bytes.

@image	html	fbf-10bitrawcion-75.png

See the Knowledgebase article <https://sdksupport.aja.com/index.php?/Knowledgebase/Article/View/145>
"How to Capture Raw Bayer Data from the CION Camera" for detailed information about capturing raw
CION data using NTV2 devices. The \ref ntv2qtrawcapture demonstration app in the SDK also shows how to capture raw video into 'DNG' files.

